NOTE ON 4T/8T DATA RELIABILITY:
The GitHub Actions macos-14 runner reports "Apple M1 (Virtual)" — a virtualized
environment with an unknown physical core count. The catastrophic throughput collapse
at 4T (1933→4.41 t/s) and 8T (0.71 t/s) is consistent with thread oversubscription
on a runner with fewer physical cores than requested threads, NOT a real performance
characteristic of either engine. Only the 1T and 2T data points should be treated
as trustworthy for comparison purposes.

TRUSTWORTHY COMPARISON (1T, 2T only):
  1T: asmllm 288.43 t/s vs llama.cpp 1933.47 t/s — asmllm is 6.7x slower
  2T: asmllm 305.12 t/s vs llama.cpp 1821.55 t/s — asmllm is 6.0x slower

This is an honest loss. llama.cpp's CPU NEON path benefits from years of hand-tuned
NEON intrinsics, tiled matmul scheduling, and optimized memory access patterns.
asmllm's ARM64 port is a first-generation hand-written GAS assembly implementation.
